    {"id":"DATA-001","area":"data-safety","title":"Make transactional AnnotationPersistence saves serialized, atomic, uniquely-temporary and recoverable","status":"done","note":"Exclusive same-directory temporaries are flushed before atomic rename; write/rename failures preserve the prior envelope and remove temporary files. Backup recovery, revision/CAS and cross-process locks remain separate work."},
    {"id":"DATA-002","area":"data-safety","title":"Add cross-process revision/CAS checks shared by VS Code, MCP and Tauri","status":"todo"},
