    {"id":"SYNC-001","area":"sync","title":"Replace overwrite-only divergence handling with three-way per-annotation merge and persisted dirty/revision state","status":"todo"},
    {"id":"ARCH-001","area":"architecture","title":"Retire the duplicate legacy AnnotationManager lifecycle after porting clipboard and rendering responsibilities","status":"todo"},
    {"id":"ARCH-002","area":"architecture","title":"Remove duplicate legacy chat/command registrations and centralize command ownership","status":"todo","note":"Obsolete credential, search/focus, activity, edit/severity and legacy-link command aliases are removed; duplicate lifecycle/chat ownership remains to retire."},
    {"id":"ARCH-003","area":"architecture","title":"Create one application service for annotation creation/mutation so editor, Comments, AI, import, MCP and Tauri apply identical defaults and limits","status":"in_progress"},
    {"id":"ARCH-004","area":"architecture","title":"Classify every runtime-only command as a documented internal protocol or retire it, then test that no hidden legacy command shadows a public handler","status":"done","note":"The exact allow-list now contains eight typed Kanban webview protocols plus annotations.manage and annotations.navigateToPanel; a unit test rejects any unclassified runtime-only command."},
    {"id":"CONFIG-001","area":"configuration","title":"Test every public setting as actively consumed or explicitly deprecated; eliminate settings that promise inactive behavior","status":"in_progress","note":"The active 13-provider settings and Azure/local connection fields are documented and tested; annotation.claudeUseSDK remains a legacy inactive setting to deprecate or remove. The menu audit also found annotation.enableAiSuggest gated in the Tree and keybinding while the editor AI hub and Command Palette remain enabled; choose and test one consistent disabled-versus-discoverable policy."},
    {"id":"WORKSPACE-001","area":"workspace","title":"Rebuild/reroute store, persistence and watchers on folder changes and support multi-root annotation ownership","status":"todo","note":"Pending lifecycle defect: activation without a folder does not construct AnnotationPersistence or AnnotationEditorMoveController, and adding a folder later does not rebuild them. Add a no-workspace-to-add-folder contract, then either keep Move handlers always registered with explicit guidance or rebuild the transactional/move stack before exposing them."},
    {"id":"IMPORT-001","area":"data-portability","title":"Replace legacy array import/export with v2 migration, workspace remapping, dry-run preview, collision policy, transaction and CAS","status":"todo"},
    {"id":"BUG-RESOLVE-001","area":"bug","title":"Make Resolve preserve the annotation and set resolved=true instead of deleting it","status":"done"},
    {"id":"BUG-CMD-001","area":"bug","title":"Replace placeholder public Kanban column commands with guided mutations of the real column-definition and assignment stores","status":"done"},
    {"id":"BUG-CMD-002","area":"bug","title":"Inject the active annotation store and real navigation service into Review Mode and gate its actions by session state","status":"done"},
    {"id":"BUG-CMD-003","area":"bug","title":"Route public create, navigate, inspect and remove link commands through the active annotation store instead of the retired empty legacy path","status":"done","note":"A direct Extension Host test covers create, v2 persistence, navigation, outgoing/incoming inspection, remove and persisted removal; compile-tests, webpack and lint are green."},
    {"id":"BUG-CMD-004","area":"bug","title":"Make Edit, Delete, Pin, Severity, file Batch Edit and one-line Move commands guide selection when no editor is open","status":"done","note":"Commands resolve an explicit argument, then the active cursor, then a picker; Delete and file-wide Batch Edit require modal confirmation."},
    {"id":"BUG-SOURCE-CONVERT-001","area":"bug","title":"Offer ordinary trailing code comments during guided comment-to-annotation conversion instead of reporting that no comment exists","status":"done","note":"The scanner records exact UTF-16 ranges for standalone, adjacent and trailing comments with or without delimiter whitespace; strings, nested templates, regex, raw strings, heredocs, YAML scalars, SQL dollar strings, nested/unterminated blocks, BOM and CRLF are covered by regressions."},
    {"id":"BUG-SOURCE-CONVERT-002","area":"bug","title":"Prevent destructive source-comment conversion from fusing neighboring language tokens","status":"done","note":"Remove is now offered only for lexically proven line-comment ranges. Block comments and documentation blocks remain convertible with Keep, but fail closed for Remove until neighboring-token separation can be proven."},
    {"id":"BUG-SOURCE-CONVERT-003","area":"bug","title":"Deduplicate repeated same-line source comments bijectively instead of suppressing every equal message","status":"done","note":"Exact import provenance, strong and legacy markers, then line/message fallback each consume at most one matching annotation, so two equal comments on one line remain two independently selectable candidates."},
    {"id":"BUG-SOURCE-CONVERT-004","area":"bug","title":"Preserve a recoverable representation when conversion rollback rejects or cannot restore the source","status":"done","note":"Compensation now keeps or recreates the destination annotation before strict persistence if source restoration fails. Destructive reverse conversion also requires an exact lossless round trip and uses a collision-resistant marker while retaining legacy-marker compatibility."},
    {"id":"SOURCE-CONVERT-001","area":"developer-workflow","title":"Convert standalone or trailing source comments, file headers and documentation blocks into selected annotations with an explicit Keep/Remove choice","status":"done","note":"The command previews kind/range, supports multi-selection, batch-deduplicates imports, asks whether the source is copied or moved and makes both resources durable. Remove and bounded native Undo/Redo are limited to proven line-comment ranges; block and documentation comments remain available through lossless Keep."},
    {"id":"SOURCE-CONVERT-002","area":"developer-workflow","title":"Write selected annotations into language-aware source comments or documentation blocks with an explicit Keep/Remove choice, safe markers and Undo","status":"done","note":"Reverse writing is enabled only for 16 audited single-context language modes and a position proven safe by the standalone lexer. Destructive Remove additionally requires exact message round-trip equivalence, emits a 128-bit collision-resistant OOCI identity while reading legacy markers, protects preambles/directives and preserves source-before-store durability with conservative rollback and native Undo/Redo."},
    {"id":"SOURCE-CONVERT-003","area":"developer-workflow","title":"Expand language-aware source-comment conversion beyond the current 42 language IDs using parser-backed ranges and symbol-aware placement","status":"todo","note":"The lexical scanner now covers adjacent/no-space comments, multiple comments per line, nested templates/blocks and major literal forms. Parser-backed follow-up remains necessary for destructive block-comment removal and for placement in embedded, preprocessor, recipe, markup and literal contexts that cannot be proven safe lexically."},
    {"id":"SOURCE-CONVERT-004","area":"developer-workflow","title":"Enable reverse comment writing in mixed and currently Keep-only modes through syntax-aware embedded-region placement","status":"todo","note":"Reverse writing remains disabled outside the 16-mode audited allowlist, including TypeScript React, JavaScript React, Vue, PHP, markup, Make/Docker, SQL, Ruby/Perl, shell/PowerShell, YAML, Haskell, INI and Lisp/Scheme families. Import/Keep conversion remains available where scanning is safe."},
    {"id":"SOURCE-CONVERT-005","area":"developer-workflow","title":"Make destructive source conversion atomic across format-on-save, save code actions and whitespace save participants","status":"todo","note":"Version 1.4.4 fails closed before mutation when configured save participants could coalesce or rewrite the conversion edit. A future journal must model formatter and conversion undo steps without weakening source-before-store durability."},
    {"id":"SOURCE-CONVERT-006","area":"ui","title":"Store source-import deduplication fingerprints as hidden provenance rather than visible annotation tags","status":"todo","note":"The 1.4.4 fingerprint is stable, non-sensitive and now participates in one-to-one duplicate matching after annotation moves, but its tag-backed storage can still appear in tag-oriented UI and generated documentation. Move it to validated hidden metadata with backward migration."},
    {"id":"SOURCE-CONVERT-007","area":"developer-workflow","title":"Enable source-aware block-comment removal and replacement while preserving lexical token separation","status":"todo","note":"Add parser-backed neighboring-token analysis and language-correct whitespace or terminator replacement before offering Remove for block and documentation comments; Keep remains the safe supported path in 1.4.4."},
    {"id":"BUG-LINK-001","area":"bug","title":"Persist link target identity and URI so links survive moves/re-anchors and resolve correctly in multi-root workspaces","status":"done","note":"New links use targetId for navigation and cycle detection; legacy file/line records remain readable and resolve relative to the source annotation workspace."},
    {"id":"BUG-NAV-001","area":"bug","title":"Derive tree, history, linked-navigation and GitHub issue lines from canonical offsets even when the source file is closed","status":"done","note":"GitHub issue creation re-fetches the canonical annotation before saving the remote URL trace, avoiding stale mirror objects after network latency."},
    {"id":"BUG-KANBAN-001","area":"bug","title":"Harden Kanban line projection, listener lifetime, hidden-card semantics, message validation and script-data escaping","status":"done","note":"Remove from Kanban uses a dedicated hidden assignment; live updates resolve document lines and one owned subscription is disposed with the view."},
    {"id":"BUG-ACTIVATION-001","area":"bug","title":"Allow the extension, menus, trees, setup and diagnostics to activate without an open workspace folder","status":"done","note":"The in-memory runtime activates in an empty window; workspace persistence and move/drop services attach only when their prerequisites exist."},
    {"id":"ONBOARD-002","area":"onboarding","title":"Replace generic not-ready errors with explicit Open a Folder guidance for every workspace-dependent command","status":"todo","note":"Empty-window activation is safe, but the public Move Selected handler still reports the generic store-not-ready message when persistence is unavailable."},
    {"id":"BUG-STORE-001","area":"data-safety","title":"Validate a complete deserialized v2 envelope before replacing live annotation state","status":"done"},
    {"id":"BUG-REVIEW-001","area":"bug","title":"Keep F8 review navigation working with panel focus and remove duplicate navigation-stack Tree View registration","status":"done"},
    {"id":"SEC-PERSIST-001","area":"security","title":"Physically confine annotation persistence and refuse symbolic-link, junction, reparse-point and non-file targets","status":"done","note":"Load/save validate existing components without following hostile links and atomic writes use an exclusive 0600 temporary file."},
    {"id":"AI-CATALOG-001","area":"ai","title":"Align the exact 13-provider catalogue with the installed runtime and guide provider-specific connection settings","status":"done","note":"LM Studio replaces unsupported TogetherAI; Azure requires endpoint, deployment and API version; Ollama and LM Studio accept local base URLs without requiring a key."},
    {"id":"QA-SOURCE-CONVERT-001","area":"quality","title":"Validate source-comment scanning, exact ranges, Keep/Remove transactions, anchor selection, safe encoding, markers, duplicate prevention and the language catalogue","status":"done","note":"Pure coverage includes all 42 catalogue IDs, a 2,000-comment batch fingerprint regression, bijective equal-comment matching, token-fusion refusal, exact destructive round trips, collision-resistant and legacy markers, rollback rejection recovery and the 16-mode reverse-placement allowlist. Extension Host coverage exercises native Undo/Redo in both Remove directions and refuses business-state divergence."},
    {"id":"AI-CRED-001","area":"ai-security","title":"Unify AI provider selection, connection settings and credential add/update/removal across user settings and SecretStorage","status":"done","note":"Configure AI Provider & Credentials covers the exact 13-provider catalogue, provider-specific Azure/local fields, one selected credential source, confirmed complete removal and visible storage failures; Ollama and LM Studio need no key."},
